OL,3,C'We failed our colleagues,' but I was
OL,4,Cnot aware of abuse, says Harrods boss
OL,6,F"Had they been, I would, of course,
OL,7,Fhave acted immediately."
OL,9,FHe accused Mr Al Fayed of running
OL,10,FHarrod's as "his own personal fiefdom"
OL,11,Fduring this "shameful period" for the
OL,12,Fbusiness.
OL,14,F"It is now clear that he presided over
OL,15,Fa toxic culture of secrecy,
OL,16,Fintimidation, fear of repercussion and
OL,17,Fsexual misconduct," Mr Ward said.
OL,19,F"The picture that is now emerging
OL,20,Fsuggests that he did this wherever he
OL,21,Foperated.
